headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 31 points and 12 rebounds as the Denver Nuggets shook off a slow start and beat the short-handed Washington Wizards 118-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 31, Nuggets pull away from Wizards 118-104

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler stepped back onto the court in his usual time slot, midway through the fourth quarter, with the Miami Heat clinging to a one-point lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler scores 35, Heat hold off Knicks 127-120

headlines.description: — Rookie guard Andrew Nembhard had 25 points and 10 assists in his first NBA game back home in Canada, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Toronto Raptors 118-114 on Wednesday night to snap their home winning streak at seven.
headlines.shortLinkText: Back home in Canada, Nembhard nets 25 as Pacers top Raptors

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors have consecutive road wins for the first time since the NBA Finals, and a big advantage in the playoff race over the team they beat to get there last June.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors get crucial 127-125 win over Doncic, Mavs

headlines.description: — The Philadelphia 76ers played without James Harden, and then Joel Embiid departed with mild right calf tightness.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Maxey keys fast start as 76ers pound Bulls 116-91

headlines.description: — Ja Morant finished with 17 points and five assists in his return to action after a league-imposed suspension and Jaren Jackson Jr. had...
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant back, Grizzlies top Rockets, clinch 1st in Southwest

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 31 points and 14 rebounds in just 24 minutes as the NBA-leading Milwaukee Bucks rolled to a 130-94 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's big night helps Bucks trounce Spurs 130-94

headlines.description: — Trailing by a point with 7.2 seconds left, Timberwolves coach Chris Finch looked at Karl-Anthony Towns in the huddle and told him he’d get the ball with a chance to put Minnesota ahead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 22 in return as Timberwolves rally past Hawks

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 30 points, rookie Shaedon Sharpe had a career-high 24 and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Utah Jazz 127-115 on Wednesday night to stop a six-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Sharpe lead Blazers past Jazz to halt 6-game skid

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 27 points and nine rebounds Wednesday night in the Lakers' 122-111 victory over the Phoenix Suns, who were furious with the game's large free-throw disparity favoring Los Angeles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers charge to skid-snapping win over Suns, 122-111
